				<p>Deb, your choice of pasta and condiment are incredible.  Oven roasting is the best thing a cook can do to resuscitate flavour in a typical tomato.  I must agree with you, however, that cherry and grape tomatoes usually do have decent flavour au naturel.  Thanks also for telling it like it is on the breadcrumb front.  Have you ever tried making Sicilian bread crumb topping by taking your bread crumbs and toasting them with some olive oil?  It&#8217;s a poor man&#8217;s parmesan.  It&#8217;s also the way my wife and I frequently use our leftover/stale bread.  I found this recipe:<br />
